    <body>
      <trans-unit id="10854" identifier="f0b8048a27a1226486fe59be669d0210">
        <source>To add up the digits you need to start from the last digit, multiply the
last digit by 1, second to last by 3 and so on.</source>
        <target>crwdns10854:0crwdne10854:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10855" identifier="2299a0d51026d8b037354ba3d6a23666">
        <source>It then checks if the product code is valid (total number is a multiple
of 10).</source>
        <target>crwdns10855:0crwdne10855:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10856" identifier="ffdb2db7dc23da007ef98c6d491927d6">
        <source>Starting at the right-hand digit will make the formula work for a wide variety of product codes.</source>
        <target>crwdns10856:0crwdne10856:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10857" identifier="efdb494a3607d1dd6d9b5be7cac40588">
        <source>You can find the number digits in a number by using the
&lt;code&gt;scratch:length of ()&lt;/code&gt; block unders “Operators”.
For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:length of (2938339392383) //13&lt;/code&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns10857:0crwdne10857:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10858" identifier="db4c78bc8b731202711868da1cfd121e">
        <source>You can access a letter (or a digit) at a specified position in a string
(or number) by using the &lt;code&gt;scratch:letter () of []&lt;/code&gt; block under “Operators”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10858:0crwdne10858:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10859" identifier="7083909d9f979da6b89fbf6531e7efea">
        <source>For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:letter (4) of [18392819202910] //9&lt;/code&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns10859:0[18392819202910]crwdne10859:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10860" identifier="ff00c0de7f501cd86e5414ba3fccec8e">
        <source>To access the last digit of the product code, make a variable called
“index” and set it to the length of the product code.</source>
        <target>crwdns10860:0crwdne10860:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[4]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10861" identifier="4f214440dc3707e193ab564d18c8f75a">
        <source>Now the last digit of the product code can be accessed by using the
&lt;code&gt;scratch:length of ()&lt;/code&gt; block with the index variable and the product code.</source>
        <target>crwdns10861:0crwdne10861:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[4]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
